    <!-- Tutorial -->
    <string name="tutorial_title">How to Use</string>
    <string name="tutorial_text">Welcome to Iskorly \n
• Fill in Student, Subgroup 1 (Section), and Subgroup 2 (Subject/Quiz).\n
• Tap Start Scan or Import Photos to scan answer sheets.\n
• Camera: Align the answer sheet and tap Scan. After capture, crop the image to focus on answers, then confirm.\n
• Import Photos: Select one or multiple images from gallery for batch processing.\n
• A popup will show the parsed answers filtered to your answer key. Tap any value to edit if needed.\n
• Tap Confirm &amp; Score to see your score, then tap Save to store it in History.\n
• Tap Scan Again to close the popup and return to the camera.\n
\n
Setup Answer Key:\n
• Setup Answer Key to manage multiple quizzes (Slots: New/Rename/Delete/Import/Export).\n
• Add answers: enter Question # and Answer (A–Z or short text up to 40 chars) → Save.\n
\n
History &amp; Analysis:\n
• History: Expand by Quiz and Section to view results.\n
• Export CSV for sharing.\n
• Masterlist: See per-question performance and common wrong answers.\n
\n
Tips:\n
• Good lighting, flat sheet, steady frame.\n
• For handwriting: dark pen, avoid shadows, crop tightly.\n
• Review parsed answers before confirming.\n</string>
    
